  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong>, then season with a pinch of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven to roast for 30 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-risotto-with-slow-roast-tomatoes/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-risotto-with-slow-roast-tomatoes/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix </strong>in 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-risotto-with-slow-roast-tomatoes/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span>tbsp <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> and cook for 4 min until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-risotto-with-slow-roast-tomatoes/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>arborio rice</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, then cook for a further 1 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-risotto-with-slow-roast-tomatoes/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add<strong> </strong>1/3<strong> </strong>of the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it has been absorbed</p><p>Continue to add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong>, a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 15-20 min, until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-risotto-with-slow-roast-tomatoes/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>risotto</strong> from the heat and stir in the <strong>grated cheddar</strong>, <strong>clotted cream </strong>and<strong> half</strong> of the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>chives </strong>then season with <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-risotto-with-slow-roast-tomatoes/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy risotto</strong> with the <strong>slow-roast tomatoes</strong> and garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped chives</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
